fvwm is a powerful window manager.  Version 2.5.9 is an alpha
release that includes a couple of new features and bug fixes over
2.5.8.  You are welcome to upgrade and test the new features or
help stabilizing the code.  Please be aware that any features
introduced in the 2.5.x development versions may be renamed,
changed or removed without notice before 2.6.0.

This release is available at the home page: http://www.fvwm.org/.

New features:
-------------

* New MenuStyle options PopupIgnore and PopupClose.

* New configure option --disable-iconv to disable iconv support.

* New extended variables $[w.iconfile] and $[w.miniiconfile].

* New Style option Unmanaged.  Such windows are not managed by
  fvwm.

* New binding context 'U' for unmanaged windows, similar to 'R'oot.

* New option DisplayNewWindowNames to the BugOpts command.

See the ChangeLog file for all details.
